         Of course hp>mana is not a 100% thing.  I would wear a shadel bandit ring over an admantite band (75hps) anyday.</P><P> If you never get hit while pulling xp mobs then you must have a really fucking boring existence.  I never get hit when I pull Katta guards either, but you can make much better xp if you are willing to take some risks and have the hp to do it.  Saying 'I never get hit' is probably the most ignorant thing I have seen anyone say on this board since disease stops regen.  Everyone gets hit.  If you don't, you fucking suck.  End of story.  It means you are taking zero risk while xping.  You arent doing any damage at raids.  You arent traveling anywhere risky.  I think it pretty apparent that all you do is sit on your ass and camp no risk xp mobs. </P><P>You dont raid, you dont have lifeburn, you dont group or use heals if you do, you dont charm, you dont do anything, so yeah, wear whatever you like, nobody will care when you die anyway.  Us necros that do like to get the max xp, raid, solo hard named mobs, eventually have lifeburn, group and throw 500hp shadowbonds around, prefer our hp gear.</P><P> But hey if all ya wanna do is farm easy xp mobs, then like I say, dont even bother buying gear cuz it really makes no difference.  Next time you are hunting Katta guards, take off all your gear and see what happens.  You won't kill any faster or slower.  You probably will see no difference, apart from the slight bit you will lose unless you pull with Vexing at 250hp.  However, like someone else pointed out with the story about the enchanter, go and try charming something, or try soloing some tough named mobs, or go raiding, you will wish you had hp gear.  I never wish I had more int or mana.  Never. </P><P>HP does not = mana.  HP allows you to get the max use out of the mana you do have.</P><P><b><font color=blue>Retrievil Hesevil</font id=blue></b><BR><font color=red><b>58 DE Necromancer - Tallon Zek</font id=red></b><BR><font color=blue><b>56 Iksar